Be warned, if you book a standard room do not be fooled by the photos and expect a similar standard.	this was below standard for a 5* room, we had to ask 3 times for pillows and 20min wait for ice.	The buffet is well presented but is fairly standard and not at all up to the level of the Michelin-starred restaurant.	The bathroom again was small and of average standard.	The rooms are spacious, handsomely appointed, and with all you would expect at this level.	The room we were given was on the ground floor, was tiny, tired and had a very 70s looking mirrored wall.